{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"45232b98-a4e3-4dab-987e-7df1c4baffe9","content":"Analyzing crash dumps is outside the scope of the available tools here (the `dump-collect` skill is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). However, here's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (`printexception`) | Print last exception details |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `dso` (`dumpstackobjects`) | Objects on the stack |\n\n**Using Visual Studio** (Windows):\n- Open the `.dmp` file directly → click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**\n\n**Using `lldb`** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\nA typical workflow: run `clrthreads` to find the faulting thread, switch to it, then `clrstack` and `pe` to see the exception and call stack.\n\nWould you like help setting up any of these tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"366c10cb-476a-462d-a850-17a4f99ecd20","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: **analyzing or debugging dumps**, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze, not collect.\n\nI should help them directly with guidance on analyzing the dump file.","outputTokens":475},"id":"fa393ec0-24be-49cf-b3a2-55ff535579d5","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:06:59.051Z","parentId":"405066fc-a404-40b1-9a2a-cc8740684c6a"}
